ce:section.ce:para:
The synthesized samples i.e., N-C-dots, SgCN/gCN, and N-C-dots/SgCN/gCN have been utilized to examine the photocatalytic removal of RhB dye. For photocatalytic removal of 50 mL of RhB dye at a 5-ppm concentration, 0.05 g of every sample is utilized. With time (0–25 min), the absorption peak's intensity of dye (554 nm) dropped, suggesting a decline in dye content. Each one of the synthesized samples was found to exhibit negligible adsorption of dye in the absence of light. Moreover, N-C-dots/SgCN/gCN, showed the maximum photocatalytic dye decomposition, as demonstrated in Fig. 9
                        , decontaminating 99.41 % RhB dye in 25 min [Table 1
                        ]. The most likely reason is that the addition of N-C-dots raised the SgCN/gCN band gap, which decreased the likelihood of electron-hole recombination and enhanced the ternary composite's photocatalytic activity compared to its constituent NMs. Hence, N-C-dots/SgCN/gCN has been used for additional investigations.
